                  </persName>, was indicted<rs id="t18450818-1791-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18450818-1791-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18450818-1791-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="theftFromPlace"></interp> for stealing 3 feet of leaden pipe, value 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18450818-name-1129" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1129" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1129" type="surname" value="BAKER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1129" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18450818-1791-offence-1 t18450818-name-1129"></join>William Baker</persName>, and fixed to a building; and that he had been before convicted of felony.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450818-name-1130" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1130" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1130" type="surname" value="BAKER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1130" type="given" value="FRANCES JANE"></interp>FRANCES JANE BAKER</persName>
                  </hi>. I live with my father, William Baker, who keeps a beer-shop—the prisoner was a customer—he was there between three and four o'clock in the afternoon, on the 8th of Aug.—we had a piece of leaden pipe at the end of the passage—I saw the prisoner pat it into his pocket, and go away—it has not been found since—I am quite sure I saw him take it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Why did not you stop me? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> My mother and father both being out, I had two businesses to attend to, and it quite slipped my memory—my father missed some taps, and he asked me about the pipe—I told him I saw the prisoner put it in his left-hand pocket—I swear he took it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450818-name-1131" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1131" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1131" type="surname" value="ROPER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1131" type="given" value="CHARLES JOHN"></interp>CHARLES JOHN ROPER</persName>
                  </hi>. I was in the house—I went into the ground to play at skittles—I saw the prisoner come, take two pieces of lead<lb></lb>pipe in his hand, and leave the ground—I thought he was a plumber.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I was passing the house, and was called in, and saw Baker's brother—he asked me to drink—I stopped there two or three hours—they were cheating a lad at cards—I mentioned it, and Baker got</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184508180194"></xptr>
               <p>up, and said, "You don't want your head punched?"—I know nothing about the pipe.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450818-name-1132" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-1132" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
